---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ContentFooter from '../components/ContentFooter.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <syn-card>
    <h1 class="syn-heading--2x-large" slot="header">Brand support and versions</h1>

    <p>
      This page describes the brand versions supported by the Synergy Design System and how they relate to components, assets, and documentation.
      It is <strong>non-normative</strong> and does not define component behavior or API contracts.
    </p>

    <h2 class="syn-heading--large">Supported brand versions</h2>
    <p>Synergy currently supports two SICK brand versions:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>SICK 2025 (current)</strong><br>
        The default and actively maintained brand version.
        All new components, features, and visual updates target this brand.
        New applications must use this brand version to access the latest design and functionality improvements.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>SICK 2018 (legacy)</strong><br>
        Supported to ensure compatibility with existing applications.
        No new features are introduced for this brand version.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="syn-heading--large">What “current” and “legacy” mean</h2>
    <p>
      A <strong>current</strong> brand version is the primary target for ongoing development and documentation.
      A <strong>legacy</strong> brand version remains supported to avoid breaking existing products, but primarily receives compatibility maintenance.
    </p>

    <h2 class="syn-heading--large">Impact on components and APIs</h2>
    <p>Brand versions affect <strong>visual appearance</strong> and <strong>assets</strong> such as icons, colors, and typography.</p>

    <p>Brand versions do <strong>not</strong> change:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>component APIs and attributes</li>
      <li>events and behavior</li>
      <li>accessibility requirements</li>
      <li>supported usage rules</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="syn-heading--large">How to read the documentation</h2>
    <p>
      Unless explicitly stated otherwise, documentation and examples reflect the <strong>SICK 2025</strong> brand version.
      Differences in appearance between applications may be the result of using the legacy SICK 2018 brand.
    </p>

    <h2 class="syn-heading--large">Migration and evolution</h2>
    <p>
      Synergy provides tooling and guidance to support migration between brand versions where applicable.
      Migration strategies and timelines are documented separately and are not defined on this page.
    </p>

    <ContentFooter
      creationDate={new Date().toISOString()}
      entityId={null}
    >
      | Normative component behavior and API contracts are defined on individual component pages.
    </ContentFooter>
  </syn-card>
</Layout>
